President Muhammadu Buhari is presently meeting with Members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) National Working Committee, NWC. BusinessDay Villa sources said the President and the ruling party’s NWC are meeting to resolve challenges facing the party arising from the outcome of the last election. Insider source disclosed the some of the party officials are unhappy with the party’s National Chairman over his alleged “one-man” administrative approach in dealing with issues affecting the party. They are also said to be unhappy that the party National Chairmen hardly calls members for meetings. BusinessDay also gathered that the meeting will be used by the President to brief the party officials as well as review the “Next Level” government policies ahead of the forthcoming inauguration of the Cabinet which will signal the formal kick-off of the President’s second tenure. Details later.. 